          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Houthi’s retaliatory operation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">A rocket fired by Yemen's Houthi rebels <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-5-struck-tel-aviv" target="_blank">struck Tel Aviv</a> overnight, injuring 16 from shattered glass and 14 others rushing to shelters during air raid sirens. The Houthis claimed they targeted a military site with a hypersonic ballistic missile. Israel's military acknowledged that its aerial defense was not sealed. The attack follows <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-6-israeli-airstrikes" target="_blank">Israeli airstrikes</a> on Houthi-controlled areas, including Sanaa and Hodeida, which killed at least nine people. A US fighter jet was accidentally <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-7-shot-down" target="_blank">shot down</a> by friendly fire over the Red Sea after the USS Gettysburg mistakenly targeted it during a mission involving airstrikes against Houthi militants in Yemen.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israel reports over 200 Houthi-launched missiles and drones during the Israel-Hamas war. The conflict between Israel and Yemen has caused significant damage to Houthi-controlled Red Sea ports vital for Yemen's food shipments. Yemen is still in the midst of a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-8-civil-war" target="_blank">civil war</a>, and the situation there continues to worsen while most of it is under Houthi rule.</p>
        </mj-text>
