          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇷🇺 Russia:</strong>    
          During his annual end-of-year conference, President Vladimir Putin <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-9-emphasized" target="_blank">emphasized</a> Russia's resilience despite challenges in Syria and Ukraine. He believes Russia has made significant progress in Ukraine and is moving towards greater sovereignty. Putin openly expressed his readiness to meet with Donald Trump amid a potential negotiation to end the war in Ukraine. Additionally, he addressed the recent death of a Russian general and acknowledged military cooperation with North Korea while downplaying the involvement of North Korean troops in the conflict in Ukraine.</p>
        </mj-text>
