          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇮🇹 Italy:</strong>   
          An Italian court <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-dec-2024-10-acquitted" target="_blank">acquitted</a> Deputy Prime Minister Matteo Salvini of charges related to the illegal detention of 100 migrants aboard the Open Arms rescue ship in 2019 when he served as interior minister. The case centered on his refusal to allow the migrants to disembark on Lampedusa Island. Now serving as Italy's transport minister, Salvini defended his actions by stating that they were aimed at protecting Italy's borders. However, the verdict is not final and could be appealed. Matteo Salvini has been one of the most outspoken voices in Europe against migration.</p>
        </mj-text>
